attributes.value: / These are kept separate from ink core utilities to allow for more dynamic inter-crate dependencies.
/ The main problem is that today Cargo manages crate features on a per-crate basis instead of
/ a per-crate-target basis thus making dependencies from `ink_lang` (or others) to `ink_env` or `ink_storage` impossible.
/ By introducing `ink_primitives` we have a way to share utility components between `ink_env` or `ink_storage` and
/ other parts of the framework, like `ink_lang`.

defs.name: Key
defs.docs: A key into the smart contract storage.

attributes.value: / A key into the smart contract storage.
/ - The storage of an ink! smart contract can be viewed as a key-value store.
/ - In order to manipulate its storage an ink! smart contract is required
/   to indicate the respective cells using this primitive type.
/ - The `Key` type can be compared to a raw pointer and also allows operations
/ - Users usually should not have to deal with this low-level primitive themselves
/   and instead use the more high-level primitives provided by the `ink_storage`

attributes.value: / This implementation is heavily optimized for little-endian Wasm platforms.
/ Since we are operating on little-endian we can convert the underlying `[u8; 32]`
/ array to `[u64; 4]`. Since in WebAssembly `u64` is supported natively unlike `u8`
/ it is more efficient to work on chunks of `u8` represented as `u64`.

/ This wraps a base key and provides an interface to mimic pointer arithmetic.
/ Mainly used to coordinate keys through static storage structures.
